<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2514] ExpandoMetaClass returns expando properties twice</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2514</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;i like to use the ExpandoMetaClass to add properties and methods during runtime.&lt;br/&gt;
For testing purposes I wrote:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class Foo{&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;}&lt;br/&gt;
println Foo.metaClass&lt;br/&gt;
def a1 = new Foo();&lt;br/&gt;
println a1.metaClass.class&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Foo.metaClass.expando = true;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;println Foo.metaClass.class&lt;br/&gt;
def a2 = new Foo();&lt;br/&gt;
println a2.metaClass.class&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a2.metaClass.test = &quot;value&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
println a2.test&lt;br/&gt;
println a2.metaClass.properties.name&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately &quot;println a2.metaClass.properties.name&quot; returns &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;expando&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;test&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;class&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;expando&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;metaClass&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;test&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is related to the getProperties method in ExpandoMetaClass:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public List getProperties() &lt;/p&gt;
{
        List propertyList = new ArrayList();
        propertyList.addAll(expandoProperties.values());
        propertyList.addAll(super.getProperties());
        return propertyList;
    }

&lt;p&gt;At first it reads the properties form the local list and adds the properties for MetaClassImpl afterwards. Why are all expando properties are hold twice?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
